About this hotel

This upscale beachfront hotel on the Bay of Tangier is 6 km from both Kasbah Museum and Dar-el-Makhzen, a former Sultan's palace.

Check-in time: 2:00 PM
Check-out time: 12:00 PM

  • Pool
  • Spa

    The location is good and most rooms would have a nice bay view. The property, however, is in need of a face-lift. Furniture is dated, etc. As an American, I felt like they had some bizarre policies. I apparently booked for one guest but …
    The location is good and most rooms would have a nice bay view. The property, however, is in need of a face-lift. Furniture is dated, etc. As an American, I felt like they had some bizarre policies. I apparently booked for one guest but when I showed up with my husband I was told I'd need to pay an extra $20/night. I've never been told that anywhere. No status recognition for the All Accor program. I travel a lot and appreciate this.
    They also don't let you order in food. Compare this to marriott who gives you bonus points when you order ubereats to one of their properties. Granted, Tanger doesn't have a ton of high end hotel options but I'd likely try the Hilton next time. Breakfast buffet was very nice, points for that.

    2/5
    Good building let down significantly by:
    Poor air conditioning the whole building felt a bit damp and our room never …
    Good building let down significantly by:
    Poor air conditioning the whole building felt a bit damp and our room never cooled below 25c (in late Oct).
    Staff were largely indifferent. Very busy having discussions with each other front of house while ignoring and even obstructing guests. It felt like a case of too many people wanting to be manager and nobody wanting to do the hospitality thing.
    Food was middling. Only one totally overworked person trying to manage the whole breakfast area. She really did as much as one could possibly expect of a lone person, while other members of staff were milling around in the background playing at manager (see above). The result was tables not being cleared as people left leaving later arrivals for breakfast to clear and set tables themselves from unused isolated place settings. Omelet undercooked with lots of uncooked egg white. Flies on the food. Nowhere for non smokers to eat which was free of smoke.
    Charging for Internet access. The only place we stayed in Morocco which did this.
    No locks on the balcony doors.
    With the right (small!) senior management team and fixed a/c this place could be really great.

I am told an upgrade to a "King size" bed suite, it was a normal room with a normal bed. No hot drink in the shoor breakfast formula, no bread!!! there was jam though. The hot water takes several minutes to arrive, noise in the hallway, in the morning at 9:15 am we open our door while we were in bed! We got up with a start. The carpet is stained.. the balcony door is not airtight and lets in the cold air and the noise of the wind.. When paying the bill, they try to make us pay 180 € instead of the 129 € announced on booking without checking if we had a reduction or not! No commercial gesture was made despite these errors...

En ce qui concerne le petit déjeuner,  les serveurs sont professionnels et serviables,  le buffet est très moyen et améliorer en effet les légumes et fruits ne sont pas exposées dans des bacs et à la bonne température,  les plats proposés ne sont pas digne d'un chef de cuisine.  J'attire votre attention sur le parking,  ne garez pas votre voiture 🚗 à  côté des arrosoirs automatiques,  sinon vous allez la retrouver dans état lamentable, les vitres et la carrosserie de ma voiture ont été arrosés,  je me suis servi de google Maps pour trouver un lavage de voiture, tous les produits de lavage ont été utilisés pour supprimer cette saleté sans résultat, j'etais tellement dégoûté, j'ai  signalé le problème à la directrice de l'accueil qui m'a acceuili avec froideur et elle m'a dit que ce n'est pas elle qui s'occupe de ce genre de problèmes, mais quelle professionnalisme vraiment médiocre, n écrit à été envoyé à la direction générale de l’hôtel.En résumé : je préfère prendre une chambre dans un Hôtel 2 étoiles avec du personnel accueillant, sympathiques et souriants que de prendre une chambre dans un Hôtel cinq étoiles 🌟  avec des personnes qui font leurs travail sans aucune attention donnée au client ,je ne vous le recommande pas.

For the price and being a 5-star hotel we expected better service (somewhat slow) and cleanliness, but it is still very high compared to Moroccan standards.     About this hotel

    This upscale beachfront hotel on the Bay of Tangier is 6 km from both Kasbah Museum and Dar-el-Makhzen, a former Sultan's palace. …

    Beachcomber-chic rooms feature free Wi-Fi, flat-screen TVs and minibars. They also come with balconies or terraces overlooking the gardens and/or the sea. Refined suites add separate living rooms, and some have dining rooms. A massive top-tier suite has a private nightclub.

    Free buffet-style breakfast is served in a Swiss-influenced restaurant with a summer terrace; an ornate second restaurant offers Moroccan fare. There's also a lobby bar, a gym and a casino, plus an outdoor pool and gardens.

    Check-in time: 2:00 PM
    Check-out time: 12:00 PM
